## Testing plan

Gates that apply: `build`, `unit-tests`, `constructor-unit-tests`.

- `build`: solution builds with the new Storage files registered and the schema content item build-copied; JsonSchema.Net/FSharp.Data/ClosedXML package refs resolve.
- `unit-tests`: existing `BerremanTests` stays green (`count_at_least` baseline from the prior slice's state-of-the-world).
- `constructor-unit-tests`: the gate command MUST cover the storage tests. `RoundTripTests.fs` (AC-I1 save→open identity; AC-I2 schema-violation→`SchemaValidationError`; AC-I3 wrong `schemaVersion` rejected, no migration); `SidecarTests.fs` (AC-A6/AC-I4 `.binz` write/read identity; AC-I5 missing sidecar→`SidecarMissing`/`BinzError`; project-through-`writeSidecar` absent); `HistoryTests.fs` (AC-I7 undo/redo identity + empty no-op; AC-I6 autosave leaves `.ocproj` untouched); `ExportImportTests.fs` (AC-I8 CSV shape; AC-I10 import/export materials; AC-I11 `appendRevision` ×2 + `diffRevisions`).
- Emit the state-of-the-world file with the `gates:` YAML baseline block.

## Risks

- **Medium:** the JSON Schema must validate every part's filled `$defs` (B/C/E/H field shapes) AND reject a wrong `schemaVersion` without migration (AC-I3); a too-loose schema lets invalid projects bind, a too-tight one rejects valid round-trips (AC-I1/AC-I2). Validate the schema against a representative project produced by the prior slices.
- **Medium:** round-trip identity (AC-I1) requires FSharp.SystemTextJson to handle every DU/record/option the aggregate now carries (`ConstructorElement`, `BeamBranch`, `Substrate`, `Thickness`, `WaveLength`, `SourceSpec`, `ChartSettings`, curved-element fields) without lossy conversion. Test with a project exercising all of them.
- **Low:** the `.gitignore` edit must scope `*.binz`/`*.autosave` to project working folders and keep `.ocproj` committable (I.3/I.4/I.5).

## Hand-off

State carried to later slices:
- The storage assembly is complete: `Errors.fs` (`StorageError`), `SchemaValidation.fs` (validate-on-load), `ProjectFile.fs` (`saveProject`/`openProject` — the single project-open seam), `Sidecar.fs` (`.binz` write/read), `RecentFiles.fs`/`Autosave`, `History.fs` (`EditHistory`), `Export.fs` (CSV/Excel/image), `Report.fs` (report + material library import/export + design history/diff).
- Part J (slice 010) routes template loads (§J.3) and gallery loads (§J.11) through `openProject`; the autosave timer/trigger and `JobRunner` (§J.10) drive `writeAutosave` and the long-running `Report.generate`; the recent-files list renders under File ▸ Recent; `EditHistory` is the multi-level undo Part B §B.10 deferred.
- The `.binz` sidecar wrappers serve Part F sweeps (slice 006) and Part G fit histories (slice 007); the `*.binz`/`*.autosave` `.gitignore` entries are in place.
- The JSON Schema validate-on-load now guards every part's `$defs`.

Per `arc-runner.system-md`, emit the state-of-the-world file with a fenced YAML `gates:` block:

```yaml
gates:
  berreman_unit_tests: <int>
```
